==Polish==
{{wikipedia}}
===Pronunciation===
/{{IPAchar|ʐɛtʂpɔsˈpɔʎita}}/

===Noun===
'''rzeczpospolita'''{{f}} {{s}}
#[[republic]] or [[commonwealth]] (abbrev. rzplita), nearly always in reference to the official name of the Republic of Poland, ''Rzeczpospolita [[polska|Polska]]'' (abbrev. ''RP''). Other examples: ''Rzeczpospolita Obojga Narodów'' Commonwealth of Poland and Lithuania, ''Polska Rzeczpospolita Ludowa ''Polish People's Republic (abbrev. ''PRL''). See [[w:Rzeczpospolita|Rzeczpospolita]] for other usages.
# [[w:Rzeczpospolita (newspaper)|''Rzeczpospolita'']], daily nationwide newspaper in Poland.

===Declension===
''rzeczpospolita'' (''[[rzecz]]'' {{f}} noun &ndash; "thing", ''[[pospolity|pospolita]]'' adj. &ndash; "common") is a [[calque]] translation of the [[Latin]]  ''[[w:res publica|res publica]]'' ("public affair"). It may be [[decline#Verb|declined]] either as two separate words or as one word (adjective). The former declension is often used to refer to the State, the latter &ndash; to the newspaper. 

